subSubSection.paragraph:
Male: Protarsi dilated. Anterior claws unequal in length (
Fig. 29d,e
): the outer flattened dorsoventrally in the apical half, with tip acuminate. Median lobe of aedeagus (

Fig. 
29g

) with apical fourth rather abruptly bent downward in lateral view. Parameres (
Fig. 29 f
) elongate, not sinuate dorsally.

Female: Slightly duller. Preapical denticles of elytra slightly more developed (
Fig. 29c
).
